protected  boolean checkIfRange(java.io.File file)
          Checks if If-Range value satisfies either of these conditions:
- it is an HTTP-Date and is after or equals to the file modification time (that is, the file is unchanged);
- it is a list of e-tags and one of them matches the file e-tag;
- no If-Range header present or the header value is *
If either of these conditions are satisfied, the function returns true, otherwise it returns false.

isLocked

protected boolean isLocked(java.io.File file)
Checks if the file is locked.

Parameters:
file - file to check for locks
Returns:
true if file is locked, false otherwise. The file is locked when there are locks on the file itself that are not included in the If header, or there are locks on any of its parent collections that are not included in the If header.

protected int authorizeFromDB(java.lang.String accessMode)
attempts to perform authorization against XML-formatted user database specified by user_db DAD parameter. Note that this method adds dependencies on SAXPath and Jaxen as it uses XPath to match against the user database.

Returns:
AUTH_NO_CREDENTIALS if authorization failed due to error or missing credentials
AUTH_WRONG_CREDENTIALS if supplied credentials didn't match
AUTH_SUCCESS if authorization passed

authenticate

protected int authenticate()
authenticate user from Authorization HTTP header. The only supported authorization method is Basic.

Returns:
AUTH_NO_CREDENTIALS if authentication failed due to error or missing credentials, in addition 401 Authorization Required is sent automatically
AUTH_WRONG_CREDENTIALS if authentication failed due to credentials mismatch, in addition 403 Forbidden response is sent automatically
AUTH_SUCCESS if authentication was successful

checkIfMatch

protected boolean checkIfMatch(java.io.File file)

checkIfRange

protected boolean checkIfRange(java.io.File file)
Checks if If-Range value satisfies either of these conditions:
- it is an HTTP-Date and is after or equals to the file modification time (that is, the file is unchanged);
- it is a list of e-tags and one of them matches the file e-tag;
- no If-Range header present or the header value is *
If either of these conditions are satisfied, the function returns true, otherwise it returns false.

checkIfNoneMatch

protected boolean checkIfNoneMatch(java.io.File file)
Checks if none of supplied e-tags in If-None-Match header match the e-tag of the entity.

Parameters:
file - resource to check against.
Returns:
true if and only if If-None-Match header contains * special character or one of the supplied e-tags match the resource e-tag.
